    {
      "_id": "card_1772975835410",
      "title": "Research: Programmatic Gumroad Notion Template Uploads",
      "description": "Research completed. Full report: ~/.openclaw/workspace/research/gumroad-notion-template-automation.md\n\n## Key Findings\n\n**The Gumroad API CANNOT create products** — only update/delete existing ones. Browser automation is required.\n\n**Good news for Notion templates**: No file upload needed — just paste a Notion duplicate link as product content. This eliminates the hardest part of browser automation.\n\n**Recommended approach**: \n1. Headless browser (persistent Playwright profile) to create product shell\n2. Paste Notion duplicate link as product content (no file upload)\n3. Use Gumroad API to update metadata afterward\n\n**Gumroad is open source** (github.com/antiwork/gumroad) — could study/extend internal API.\n\n**Next steps:** Build automation script using agent-browser with persistent login profile.",
      "labels": [
        "research",
        "automation",
        "gumroad"
      ],
      "priority": "High",
      "column": "done",
      "order": 29,
      "createdAt": 1772975835410,
      "updatedAt": 1774277450525,
      "executorStatus": "completed",
      "completedAt": 1773118753782
    },
