    {
      "title": "Install Claude Code skills (Everything Claude Code)",
      "description": "Install and set up all Claude Code skills\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-07 15:24)\nEverything is installed. Here's my summary:\n\n---\n\n**Task Complete: Claude Code Skills Already Installed**\n\nAll **242 Claude Code skills** are fully installed at `~/.claude/skills/`, plus **32 GSD commands** at `~/.claude/commands/gsd/`. This is the complete \"Everything Claude Code\" collection.\n\n**What's available:**\n\n- **Core workflow skills**: `brainstorming`, `deep-research`, `executing-plans`, `writing-plans`, `verification-before-completion`, `subagent-driven-development`, `dispatching-parallel-agents`, `using-superpowers`\n- **Development skills**: Python, TypeScript, React, Next.js, Go, Rust, .NET, and more — covering testing, patterns, performance, packaging, and architecture\n- **DevOps/Infra**: Terraform, Kubernetes, Helm, GitOps, CI/CD (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI), Prometheus, Grafana, service mesh (Istio, Linkerd)\n- **Security**: SAST, secrets management, GDPR, PCI compliance, memory forensics, binary analysis, Solidity security, attack trees, STRIDE analysis\n- **Product/Business**: Resume tools, career skills, startup frameworks, product strategy, McKinsey strategy, financial modeling, KPI dashboards\n- **Document creation**: PDF, DOCX, PPTX, XLSX generators\n- **Playwright testing**: init, generate, fix, review, coverage, report, migrate, BrowserStack, TestRail\n- **Meta skills**: `skill-creator`, `remember`, `status`, `promote`, `extract`\n- **GSD project management**: 32 slash commands for structured project execution\n\n**How to use them**: Type `/skill-name` in Claude Code (e.g., `/brainstorming`, `/deep-research`, `/gsd:new-project`). They're all listed in your slash command menu. No dashboard needed for this — it's a tool configuration, not something with data to monitor.",
      "labels": [
        "skills",
        "claude-code"
      ],
      "priority": "High",
      "column": "done",
      "order": 26,
