    {
      "title": "Analyze Instagram Reel & Research Viability",
      "description": "Analyze this Instagram reel and research if it's a good business idea:\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DVbbLCxkWOW/?igsh=MXBkN3hlbHV0Mzk0Ng==\n\n**Task:**\n1. Use instaloader skill to extract the reel details and caption\n2. Understand what the creator is doing\n3. Research the concept\n4. Analyze viability as a business:\n   - Market demand\n   - Monetization potential\n   - Competitive landscape\n   - Barriers to entry\n   - Scalability\n5. Assess if it's something Joe should pursue\n6. If promising, add to passive income database\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- Summary of what the reel shows\n- Viability assessment\n- Pros & cons\n- Recommendation (pursue / skip / research more)\n- If viable: add to passive income database with details\n\n**Tools:** Use instaloader to get caption and metadata\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-08 21:38)\ne 550+ videos per day at ~$300/month in tool costs, replacing what would be a $500K+/year human content team. The videos get posted to TikTok Shop with affiliate product links.\n\n---\n\n**Viability Assessment:**\n\n| Factor | Rating | Notes |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Market Demand | High | TikTok Shop growing fast, brands desperate for UGC content |\n| Monetization | Medium-High | Affiliate model = no inventory risk, commission on every sale |\n| Competition | Medium-High | Getting crowded as AI tools become mainstream |\n| Barriers to Entry | Low | ~$300/month in tools, no special skills needed |\n| Scalability | Very High | AI = near-zero marginal cost per video |\n| Platform Risk | High | TikTok bans, AI detection, policy changes |\n| Realism Score | 6/10 | Income claims likely inflated; real results vary widely |\n\n**Pros:**\n- Near-zero cost per video vs $200-500 for human creators\n- Affiliate-only means no inventory, shipping, or customer service\n- Can test hundreds of product niches cheaply\n- Highly automatable pipeline\n\n**Cons:**\n- TikTok could crack down on AI-generated content at any time\n- Market is getting saturated — Noah's own audience is learning this exact playbook\n- AI avatar quality is still \"uncanny valley\" for many viewers\n- FTC requires clear affiliate/AI disclosure, which hurts conversion\n- Income claims from gurus are typically top 1% results\n\n**Recommendation: Research More**\n\nThe concept is legit but overhyped. The affiliate-only path is low-risk enough to test — spend $100-200 on ArcAds, make 50 videos in one niche, and see what actual conversion looks like before committing. Don't expect $5K/month out of the gate; $500-1K is more realistic for a solo operator. The real money is in running an agency like Noah does (selling the service to brands), not in doing affiliate yourself.\n\nI added this as a new idea to your passive income database in Mission Control (visible at `/app/passive-ideas`) with full details, tags, and build instructions for Claude.",
