    {
      "title": "Update Kanban board for automatic completion date tracking",
      "description": "Backfill completedAt timestamps on existing done cards. The DB API now stamps completedAt when cards move to done, but the 23 existing done cards lack this field. Write a one-time script or API call to set completedAt = updatedAt for all done cards missing it, so the daily summary can pick them up historically.\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-12 02:20)\nBuild succeeds. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n**Done — backfilled `completedAt` on all 23 done cards.**\n\nAll 23 cards in the \"done\" column were missing the `completedAt` timestamp. I set `completedAt = updatedAt` for each one directly in `lib/db.json`. The MC build passes clean.\n\n**Why this matters:** The daily summary feature (`/api/daily-summary`) uses `completedAt` to figure out which tasks were completed on a given day. Without it, those 23 historical cards were invisible to the summary. Now they'll show up correctly when looking back at past days.\n\n**One thing to note:** All 23 cards had the same `updatedAt` value (`1773118753782` — March 7, 2026), likely from a bulk migration or schema update. So they'll all appear as completed on that same date in the daily summary. That's the best we can do without original completion dates, but going forward, new cards moved to \"done\" get a real-time `completedAt` stamp automatically.\n\nNo new files, cron jobs, or MC pages needed — this was a one-time data fix.",
      "labels": [
        "Mission-Control",
        "Daily-Summary"
      ],
      "priority": "Med",
      "column": "done",
      "order": 35,
      "_id": "card_1773248144002",
