    {
      "_id": "card_1773297500652",
      "title": "Find a way to create a persistent connection to Google Search Console",
      "description": "Google blocks automated browser logins (\"This browser or app may not be secure\"). Need a way to authenticate and maintain a session for GSC tasks like sitemap submission and indexing requests.\n\nOptions to explore:\n- Google Search Console API + OAuth2 service account or refresh token\n- Add webmasters/searchconsole scope to gog CLI\n- Persistent browser profile with pre-authenticated Google session\n\nBlocked tasks:\n- Submit blog sitemap (blog-posts-sitemap.xml) for mastermindshq.business\n- Request indexing on key pages (homepage, VSL, services, about, top blog posts)\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-12 17:17)\nhat I built:** A full `gsc` CLI tool for Google Search Console management.\n\n**Files created/modified:**\n- **`~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/seo-monitor/src/gsc-actions.js`** — New GSC management tool with 11 commands: sites, sitemaps, submit-sitemap, delete-sitemap, index, remove, index-status, inspect, batch-index, auth, status\n- **`~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/seo-monitor/src/gsc-auth.js`** — Upgraded OAuth scopes from `webmasters.readonly` to `webmasters` (read/write) + `indexing` (URL indexing requests)\n- **`~/bin/gsc`** — CLI wrapper so you can run `gsc <command>` from anywhere\n- **`~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/seo-monitor/SETUP-GSC-WRITE.md`** — Quick setup guide\n\n**What works now (read operations):**\n- `gsc status` — shows auth status and scope coverage\n- `gsc sites` — lists your 2 verified properties (mastermindshq.business, theconnectionmap.com)\n- `gsc sitemaps` — shows submitted sitemaps (currently just sitemap.xml)\n- `gsc inspect <url>` — checks any URL's indexing status (I found your /services page is \"Discovered - currently not indexed\" — good candidate for indexing request)\n\n**What needs your one-time action (~2 min):**\n\nGoogle blocks automated browsers (\"This browser or app may not be secure\"), so I couldn't complete the OAuth consent automatically. You need to do this once:\n\n1. **Enable the Indexing API**: Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library?project=141906476123, search \"Web Search Indexing API\", click Enable\n2. **Run `gsc auth`**: Opens your real browser, sign in with newyork1@gmail.com, click Allow. Token saves automatically.\n\nAfter that, these commands unlock and the blocked tasks can run:\n```\ngsc submit-sitemap https://www.mastermindshq.business/blog-posts-sitemap.xml\ngsc batch-index https://www.mastermindshq.business/ https://www.mastermindshq.business/services https://www.mastermindshq.business/about\n```\n\nOnce you've done the re-auth, just tell me and I'll immediately submit the blog sitemap and request indexing on your key pages.",
      "labels": [
        "seo",
        "google",
        "infrastructure"
      ],
      "priority": "Med",
      "column": "done",
      "order": 18,
      "createdAt": 1773297500652,
