      "description": "Add YouTube Data API v3 key to enable deeper analytics on YouTube channel performance.\n\n## Steps\n1. Go to Google Cloud Console (newyork1@gmail.com)\n2. Enable YouTube Data API v3\n3. Create API key (or OAuth credentials for private data like revenue)\n4. Add to ~/.openclaw/workspace/.env as YOUTUBE_API_KEY\n5. Connect to the YouTube analytics MC page\n\n## Unlocks\n- Subscriber trends over time\n- Video performance (views, watch time, CTR)\n- Revenue data (requires OAuth, not just API key)\n- Channel growth tracking in Mission Control",
