      "completedAt": 1773504884037
    },
    {
      "_id": "card_whoop_dashboard_001",
      "title": "Create WHOOP health dashboard page in MC",
      "description": "Create a new dashboard page under Personal > Health called \"WHOOP\" that displays useful metrics:\n\n**Daily Metrics to Show**:\n- Recovery Score (0-100 with color coding)\n- Strain Score (0-21 with activity indicator)\n- Sleep Duration & Quality (hours + stage breakdown)\n- Heart Rate Variability (HRV trend)\n- Resting Heart Rate (trend)\n- Respiratory Rate\n\n**Weekly/Trends**:\n- 7-day recovery trend chart\n- 7-day strain trend chart\n- Sleep quality consistency\n- Optimal recovery times\n\n**Setup**:\n1. Create /app/health/whoop page component\n2. Add data fetching hook to pull from WHOOP agent\n3. Create stats cards with real-time data\n4. Add trends/charts (using charting library)\n5. Link in MC sidebar under Personal > Health\n\n**After WHOOP agent is ready** - depends on agent setup task",
      "labels": [
        "whoop",
        "dashboard",
        "health",
        "ui"
      ],
      "priority": "High",
      "column": "backlog",
      "order": 13,
      "createdAt": 1773487608000,
      "updatedAt": 1773744972897
    },
    {
      "title": "1) Fix Whoop nav — nest it under Personal in the sidebar. 2) Look at the Whoop MC page, take a snapshot, and make it way better to look at, ideally exactly like Whoop looks.",
      "column": "review",
      "order": 6,
      "_id": "card_1773499395620",
      "createdAt": 1773499395620,
      "updatedAt": 1774167680645,
      "executorStatus": "completed",
      "description": "\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-15 07:49)\nBoth tasks done. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n**What I did:**\n\n1. **Fixed the Whoop sidebar nav** — The WHOOP page was floating as a top-level item in the sidebar because the server-side nav state (`~/.openclaw/workspace/data/nav-state.json`) had `/app/whoop` in the `topLevel` array instead of nested under Personal. I moved it into `customChildren[\"/app/personal-info\"]` so it now appears under **Personal > WHOOP** where it belongs.\n\n2. **Completely redesigned the Whoop page** to match the actual WHOOP app aesthetic:\n   - **Dark theme** — Near-black (#0a0a0a) background, replacing the generic MC light-card style\n   - **Three circular gauges** at the top for Recovery (green/yellow/red zone-colored), Strain (blue, 0-21 scale), and Sleep Performance (purple) — with animated ring fills and subtle glow effects\n   - **Recovery zone badge** — Shows \"Green\", \"Yellow\", or \"Red\" badge in the header with matching color\n   - **Sub-metrics under each gauge** — HRV/RHR/SpO2 under Recovery, Avg HR/Max HR/Cal under Strain, Duration/Efficiency/Consistency under Sleep\n   - **Sleep stages bar** — Horizontal proportional bar with Awake (gray), Light (blue), REM (purple), Deep (indigo) segments, plus duration & percentage labels\n   - **Sleep Need breakdown** — Baseline, Sleep Debt, From Strain, Nap Offset cards\n   - **Skin temperature card** when available\n   - All typography uses tabular-nums, uppercase tracking labels, and minimal rounded-3xl cards — matching WHOOP's clean, data-forward design language\n\n**Files changed:**\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace/data/nav-state.json` — moved whoop to Personal children\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control/app/app/whoop/page.tsx` — full page redesign\n\nGo check it out at `localhost:3000/app/whoop` — it should feel much more like opening the WHOOP app now."
    },
    {
      "title": "CashClaw: AI Freelance Money Engine — Review & Decide",
      "column": "review",
      "priority": "High",
      "order": 0,
      "description": "**CashClaw is live and connected to your Stripe account.**\n\n## What Was Done\n- Cloned to ~/.openclaw/workspace/cashclaw/\n- Stripe connected: LIVE mode (newyork1@gmail.com, acct_16xK9aEmLFN6MnIW)\n- Config at ~/.cashclaw/config.json\n- 7 skills installed into ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/\n- First live Stripe payment link created: https://buy.stripe.com/8x25kDaTV9B02pTggdcEw0d ($29 SEO Audit)\n\n## Active Services\n- SEO Audit: $9 / $29 / $59\n- Blog Post: $5 (500w) / $12 (1500w)\n- Lead Gen: $9 / $15 / $25\n- Social Media: $9/wk – $49/mo\n\n## Ideas to Hit $50\n1. Share $29 SEO audit link to 2 startup founders\n2. Sell 5x blog posts at $12 to mastermind members\n3. LinkedIn post: free mini audit → $9 upsell\n4. $15 lead gen to Rio WhatsApp SMBs\n5. Connect HYRVEai marketplace for inbound\n\n## CLI\n```\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/cashclaw\nnode bin/cashclaw.js status\nnode bin/cashclaw.js invoice --client email@x.com --amount 29 --service SEO Audit\n```",
      "labels": [
        "passive-income",
        "cashclaw"
      ],
      "project": "Passive Income",
      "_id": "card_1773506662296",
