    {
      "id": "da4257da-ed9b-4b70-91e0-78400438bc67",
      "columnId": "claude-code-todo",
      "title": "Build: Human Must Do Auto-Handler (attempt tracking + playbooks)",
      "description": "## Goal\nOn every task executor run, scan **Human Must Do** column and attempt to complete tasks using agent-browser (port 9223) + LastPass + any available tools. Track attempts, split completed work into Review cards, document what works.\n\n---\n\n## Attempt Tracking (Required on Every Card)\nEach Human Must Do card gets a metadata block updated on every attempt:\n\n```\nattempts: 0 / 3\nlast_attempt: <ISO timestamp>\nlast_result: blocked — <reason>\nresearch_notes: <what was investigated>\n```\n\n- **Minimum 3 attempts** before marking truly un-automatable\n- On each block: research how to do it autonomously, install any free tools needed, document findings in the card\n- If a paid API is required → create a Backlog research card instead\n\n---\n\n## Card Lifecycle per Task\n\n1. **Attempt task** using agent-browser, LastPass, gog, wacli, gh, etc.\n2. **Fully completed** → create Review card with what was done, clear from Human Must Do\n3. **Partially completed** → Review card for parts done, update original with remaining steps\n4. **Blocked** → update attempt count, add research notes, retry next run\n5. **3 failed attempts** → leave in Human Must Do with full notes on what was tried + why it failed\n\n---\n\n## Process Memory (Log What Works)\nSave successful automation recipes to:\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/human-task-handler/playbooks/`\n\nOne markdown file per task type. Examples:\n- `wix-alt-tags.md` — download image → vision analysis → Wix API update alt text\n- `wix-seo-meta.md` — fetch page → generate meta desc → patch via Wix API\n- `form-submission.md` — agent-browser → fill fields → submit\n\nOn success: write/update the relevant playbook so future runs skip the discovery step.\n\n---\n\n## Wix SEO / Alt Tags (Likely Fully Automatable)\n1. Fetch image URL from Wix media manager API\n2. Download image locally\n3. Run Claude vision analysis to describe image\n4. PATCH Wix API with generated alt text\n5. Log success to `wix-alt-tags.md` playbook\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n- [ ] `~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/human-task-handler/src/index.js`\n- [ ] Reads Human Must Do cards from db.json or MC API\n- [ ] For each card: check playbook, attempt automation\n- [ ] Updates attempt count + metadata block on card after each run\n- [ ] Creates Review card on full/partial success\n- [ ] Writes/updates playbook on success\n- [ ] Creates Backlog research card if paid API required\n- [ ] Called from `/Users/openclaw/bin/task-executor` on every run\n- [ ] Logs to `~/.openclaw/workspace/logs/human-task-handler/`\n\n---\n\n## Free Tools (Use Without Asking)\nagent-browser (port 9223), LastPass (lpass), Wix REST API, Claude CLI (vision/text), gog, wacli, gh, HuggingFace\n\n## Paid APIs → Create Backlog Research Card First\nAny new third-party SaaS API with a cost needs Joe's approval before use.",
      "order": 2,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-15T01:06:10.498422+00:00",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-15T01:12:26.617910+00:00",
      "labels": [
        "automation",
        "agent-browser"
      ],
      "priority": "high"
    },
    {
      "id": "d8610aa4-c0a1-4b1f-bc1f-f00084d154af",
      "columnId": "claude-code-todo",
      "title": "Research: Best Free CRM with WhatsApp + Email + Strong API",
      "description": "## Goal\nFind the best free CRM that can track contacts inside and outside our OS, with strong free APIs, WhatsApp + email integration, and the ability to talk to it directly via AI.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendation (Best Stack for Joe)\n\n### Option A — Three-piece stack (most powerful)\n| Tool | Role | Cost |\n|------|------|------|\n| **Twenty CRM** | Data layer, contact/deal tracking | Free (self-hosted) |\n| **Chatwoot** | WhatsApp + email omnichannel inbox | Free (self-hosted) |\n| **n8n** | Automation glue between everything | Free (self-hosted) |\n\n- Twenty: https://twenty.com / https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty\n- Chatwoot: https://chatwoot.com\n- n8n: https://n8n.io\n\n### Option B — Single system (simpler setup)\n**Frappe CRM** — WhatsApp native + email + CRM in one package, fully open-source\n- https://frappe.io/crm | https://github.com/frappe/crm\n\n---\n\n## Full CRM Comparison\n\n### 1. Twenty CRM ⭐ Best API\n- Free forever self-hosted (GPL)\n- REST + GraphQL, unlimited API calls on self-hosted\n- Auto-generates APIs from custom data models\n- WhatsApp: via Chatwoot + n8n integration (not native yet)\n- AI: wire Claude directly via GraphQL — no native LLM yet\n- https://twenty.com\n\n### 2. Frappe CRM ⭐ Best WhatsApp Native\n- Free forever self-hosted; Frappe Cloud ~$10/mo\n- Full REST API, unlimited self-hosted\n- Native WhatsApp Business API built-in (Meta official + Twilio)\n- Full email (send/receive, templates, SLAs)\n- https://frappe.io/crm\n\n### 3. Chatwoot ⭐ Best Omnichannel Inbox\n- Free self-hosted (MIT license), 500 conv/mo on cloud free\n- REST API + webhooks, no limits self-hosted\n- Native WhatsApp (official Meta + WAHA unofficial/free)\n- Built-in AI assist (wire OpenAI/Claude on self-hosted)\n- More helpdesk than CRM — best paired with Twenty\n- https://chatwoot.com\n\n### 4. Bitrix24\n- Cloud free: unlimited users, unlimited contacts, 5GB\n- REST API on free (rate limits apply)\n- WhatsApp via Twilio (extra cost ~$20+/mo for number)\n- CoPilot AI on free with limited credits\n- https://bitrix24.com\n\n### 5. Attio — Best Conversational AI Interface\n- Free: 3 seats, 50K records, 250 automation credits/mo\n- REST API on free tier\n- \"Ask Attio\" — natural language queries against your CRM data ✨\n- No WhatsApp on any plan\n- https://attio.com\n\n### 6. HubSpot — Skip for our use case\n- WhatsApp requires Professional plan (paid, expensive)\n- API rate limited on free (110 req/10s)\n- Good for email-only pipelines\n- https://hubspot.com\n\n### 7. n8n — Automation Glue\n- Self-hosted free forever\n- 400+ integrations: WhatsApp Business API, Gmail, Claude/OpenAI\n- Not a CRM itself — connects everything together\n- https://n8n.io\n\n---\n\n## What \"Talk to it Directly\" Looks Like\n- **Attio**: \"Ask Attio\" — natural language → CRM queries (best out of box)\n- **Twenty + Claude**: GraphQL API → Claude CLI → ask anything about contacts/deals\n- **n8n**: WhatsApp message → n8n → Claude → query CRM → reply back to WhatsApp\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Next Steps\n- [ ] Decide: Option A (Twenty+Chatwoot+n8n) vs Option B (Frappe CRM)\n- [ ] Set up self-hosted Docker instance\n- [ ] Connect WhatsApp Business API\n- [ ] Wire Claude/Uni as conversational interface\n\n---\n\n## Research Sources\n- https://twenty.com\n- https://frappe.io/crm\n- https://chatwoot.com\n- https://n8n.io\n- https://attio.com\n- https://marmelab.com/blog/2026/01/09/open-source-crm-benchmark-2026.html\n- https://growcrm.io/2026/01/04/top-20-open-source-self-hosted-crms-in-2025/",
      "order": 1,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-15T03:12:06.249926+00:00",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-15T03:12:06.250116+00:00",
      "labels": [
        "research",
        "crm",
        "tools"
      ],
      "priority": "medium"
    },
