    {
      "title": "Set up Ooni bot for Ronnie (Telegram)",
      "description": "**Step 1 — Create the bot (2 min, Telegram)**\n\nMessage @BotFather:\n1. Send /newbot\n2. Name: Ooni Assistant\n3. Username: ronnie_ooni_bot (or any _bot username)\n4. Copy the token\n\n---\n\n**Step 2 — Add token to .env**\n\nOpen ~/.openclaw/workspace/.env and replace:\n`RONNIE_BOT_TOKEN=PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_BOTFATHER_HERE`\n\n---\n\n**Step 3 — Start the bot**\n\n```\nlaunchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.ronnie-bot.plist\n```\n\n---\n\n**Step 4 — Get Ronnie's Telegram ID**\n\nHave Ronnie message the bot. Check log:\n```\ntail -f ~/.openclaw/logs/ronnie-bot.log\n```\nIt prints: `SETUP: First message from chat ID XXXXXXXXX`\n\nAdd to .env: `RONNIE_TELEGRAM_ID=XXXXXXXXX`\n\nThen restart:\n```\nlaunchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.ronnie-bot.plist && launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.ronnie-bot.plist\n```\n\n---\n\n**What Ronnie gets:** Tasks, TidyCal, Slack, contacts, image gen, research\n**Blocked:** .env, LastPass, API keys, credentials",
      "labels": [
        "telegram",
        "setup"
      ],
      "priority": "Med",
      "column": "done",
      "order": 1,
      "_id": "card_1773669139205",
      "createdAt": 1773669139205,
      "updatedAt": 1774277450525,
      "completedAt": 1774277435579
    },
    {
      "column": "review",
      "title": "Build a Prettier Branded PDF Template",
      "order": 12,
      "description": "## Goal\nBuild a reusable, visually polished branded PDF template using reportlab.\n\n## To provide before starting:\n- **Logo file** (PNG, transparent preferred) — e.g. Joe Che or Mastermindshq logo\n- **Background images** — cover page bg, section dividers, or page watermark (PNG/JPG)\n- **Color palette** — currently in memory: #151515, #FCF4EB, #7C69C7, #F5C3C6 (confirm or override)\n- **Fonts** — any custom TTF font files, or confirm system fonts\n- **Reference design** — a PDF, screenshot, or Canva export showing the layout you want\n- **Page types needed** — cover page, content pages, section headers, back page?\n\n## Output\nA Python template file at ~/.openclaw/workspace/templates/pdf/branded_template.py that:\n- Accepts content as structured input\n- Renders cover, body, and optional back page\n- Embeds logo, background images, branded colors\n- Reusable for workbooks, guides, mastermind materials, etc.\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-17 00:04)\nhis is a reusable Python module (reportlab-based) that generates polished, Connection Map-branded PDFs. It uses your PP Object Sans fonts with Helvetica fallback, your full color palette (#151515, #FCF4EB, #7C69C7, #F5C3C6), and the Joe Che / mastermindshq.business branding throughout.\n\n**What it supports:**\n- **Cover page** — dark hero header with brand label, title, tagline, date, and pink accent stripe (matches your tech setup guide pattern)\n- **Content sections** with 12 block types: paragraph, numbered (purple badges), bullet, callout (purple background box), checkbox, subheading, link, Q&A, member card, image, spacer, horizontal rule, page break\n- **Section dividers** — full-page dark breaks between major parts\n- **Back page** — closing CTA with branded footer\n- **Markdown in text** — bold, italic, and URLs auto-convert to purple clickable links\n\n**Three ways to use it:**\n1. **Python import** — `from branded_template import BrandedPDF` then chain `.add_cover()`, `.add_section()`, `.add_back_page()`, `.build()`\n2. **JSON spec** — `python3 branded_template.py --json data.json` for pipeline/automation use\n3. **Demo** — `python3 branded_template.py --demo` to regenerate the sample\n\n**Customizable per-document:** title, subtitle, brand label, footer text, logo path, and output path. The defaults are all Joe Che / mastermindshq but can be overridden for any project.\n\n**Why it's useful:** Your existing mastermind scripts (`build-pdf.js`, `build-tech-requirements-pdf.js`) generate Python on-the-fly via JS string templates — hard to maintain and debug. This template is a proper Python class you can import directly. Future scripts (workbooks, guides, course materials) just pass structured data and get a polished PDF back. The JSON mode also means non-code pipelines (cron jobs, task executor) can generate PDFs from a spec file.\n\n**Demo PDF** generated at `~/.openclaw/workspace/templates/pdf/demo-branded.pdf` (49.6 KB, 4 pages) — open it to see all the features in action.",
      "_id": "card_1773672207949",
      "createdAt": 1773672207949,
      "updatedAt": 1774167680645,
      "executorStatus": "completed"
    },
    {
