    {
      "title": "Install 4 GitHub Repos + Usage Guide",
      "description": "Search GitHub for these repos, clone/install them, then produce a plain-language guide on the best ways to use each:\n\n1. **awesome-claude-code** — curated collection of Claude Code resources, skills, prompts, and extensions. Install any relevant skills/plugins into ~/.claude/skills/.\n\n2. **UI/UX Pro Max skill** — Claude Code skill for UI/UX design. Find the exact repo name (search GitHub), install as a brewcode/skill, verify it loads.\n\n3. **superpowers** — likely a Claude Code skill pack or prompt collection. Search GitHub for \"claude code superpowers\". Install and wire up. (Note: using-superpowers skill already exists locally — check if this is the same thing or an upgrade.)\n\n4. **claude-mem** — memory management tool for Claude. Search GitHub for \"claude mem\" / \"claude-mem\". Install, configure, integrate with existing ~/.claude memory system.\n\nFor each repo:\n- Find exact GitHub URL\n- Clone to ~/.openclaw/workspace/tools/ or install as appropriate\n- Document: what it does, top 3 best use cases, how Joe should invoke it\n- Add any new skills to Claude Code skill system\n- Output a summary card in MC or a markdown doc at ~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/github-tools.md",
      "column": "claude-code",
      "columnId": "claude-code",
      "order": 4,
      "_id": "card_1773748830175",
      "createdAt": 1773748830175,
      "updatedAt": 1773800783965
    },
