    {
      "column": "done",
      "title": "Research: Weather Betting App (loss-credit model, partner products)",
      "description": "Research and build out the ideas-lab/weather-betting project.\n\nCore concept: Weather prediction market (like Polymarket) where losers earn credits redeemable for partner products/samples — so you always win something.\n\nResearch tasks:\n1. Existing competitors/similar apps\n2. Smart partner businesses (sample products, free trial seekers)\n3. Regulatory landscape (gambling laws, how Polymarket operates in US, prediction market vs gambling)\n4. Variation: bet on weather → win products, partner gets email/mailing address (lead gen model)\n5. Name suggestions\n6. Best ICP + best regions (weather-obsessed communities)\n\nDeliver: RESEARCH.md, PARTNERS.md, LEGAL.md, ICP.md, NAMES.md under ~/.openclaw/workspace/projects/ideas-lab/weather-betting/\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-18 09:24)\nather markets but are finance-first. The \"lose and still get a product sample\" model is an unoccupied niche. Lootie.com's failure (mystery boxes, stopped fulfilling) is a cautionary tale — use third-party sample fulfillment networks, never hold inventory.\n\n- **PARTNERS.md** (387 lines) — 11 partner verticals with 20 high-priority targets ranked by fit. Solar leads pay $25-300/lead, flood insurance $30-80 CPL. Best phase 1 partners: digital code companies (DoorDash, HelloFresh, LMNT) to avoid physical shipping complexity. Sponsored predictions (\"Will it snow in Denver? Brought to you by North Face\") is a differentiated, low-friction ad format.\n\n- **LEGAL.md** (569 lines) — Four structural options analyzed: CFTC-regulated market, free-to-play contest, sweepstakes model, or fantasy sports-style skill game. Recommended path: launch as free-to-play sponsored contest (no licensing needed), then layer in sweepstakes dual-currency for monetization. Weather prediction has a strong \"skill game\" argument. Includes international regs and privacy/GDPR considerations for the lead-gen model.\n\n- **ICP.md** (645 lines) — 7 customer segments, 8 regions. Best launch target: ski/snowboard community in Colorado/Utah — they already pay for weather data (OpenSnow), have verifiable prediction questions, and map perfectly to partner products. Phase 2: add surf/golf/storm chasers. International: UK and Australia year 2.\n\n- **NAMES.md** (360 lines) — 40 name ideas across 7 categories. Top picks: **Windfall** (means unexpected gain + contains \"wind\"), **Raincheck** (the loss mechanic is baked into the phrase), **Hedgecast** (\"hedge your bets\" + \"forecast\"), **SilverLiner**, **WinCast**.\n\n**Next steps worth considering:**\n1. Pick a working name and check domain availability via Porkbun\n2. Build a one-page concept deck for partner outreach\n3. Validate with 5-10 ski community members (Reddit r/skiing, r/snowboarding)\n4. Talk to a gaming/sweepstakes lawyer about the free-to-play → sweepstakes path",
      "order": 53,
      "priority": "Med",
      "labels": [],
