    {
      "title": "MiroFish Installed & Wired",
      "column": "done",
      "order": 6,
      "description": "## MiroFish Setup Complete\n\n**Location:** `~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/mirofish/`\n\n### Ports\n- Frontend (Vue/Vite): **3777** (changed from 3000 to avoid MC conflict)\n- Backend (Flask): **5001**\n\n### Key Config\n- **LLM**: Routes through CLIProxyAPI at `127.0.0.1:8317` (no API credit burn)\n- **Model**: `claude-sonnet-4-6`\n- **Embeddings**: Ollama `nomic-embed-text` at `localhost:11434`\n- **Graph DB**: Neo4j at `bolt://localhost:7687` — password: `mirofish`\n- **Env file**: `backend/.env`\n- **Python venv**: `backend/.venv` (Python 3.11 — required for camel-oasis)\n\n### Polymarket Integration\n- Feed module added: `src/feeds/mirofish.js`\n- Auto-loaded by researcher.js — queries MiroFish for completed simulation reports\n- Returns empty signals gracefully if MiroFish is not running\n\n### To Start MiroFish\n```bash\n# Backend\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/mirofish/backend\nsource .venv/bin/activate && python run.py\n\n# Frontend (separate terminal)\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/agents/mirofish/frontend\nnpm run dev  # opens on :3777\n```\n\n### Known Quirks\n- Python 3.14 incompatible with camel-oasis — venv uses 3.11\n- Neo4j password was set via HTTP transaction API (cypher-shell blocked)\n- launchd plist not yet created (manual start for now)",
      "_id": "card_1773823395957",
      "createdAt": 1773823395957,
      "updatedAt": 1774277450525
    },
    {
      "column": "done",
      "order": 52,
      "title": "[Polymarket] LLM Ensemble for Crypto — Build Plan",
      "description": "## Overview\nReplace single Claude forecaster with a parallel Claude + GPT-4o ensemble for crypto markets (BTC, ETH, SOL). Based on Science Advances 2025 research: 12-model ensemble ties 925-person human crowd. Diversity of architecture/training reduces systematic bias.\n\n## Why It Works\n- Claude: conservative, anchors to base rates, underestimates momentum moves\n- GPT-4o: more aggressive, better at momentum/sentiment\n- Averaging them cancels out each model's systematic blind spots\n- Paper also shows exposing models to market price (median human estimate) → +17–28% accuracy — we already pass market price, so that's covered\n\n## What to Build\n\n### 1. Add GPT-4o path to `src/strategist.js`\n- Import OpenAI SDK (`npm install openai`)\n- Add `callGpt4oForecaster(marketContext)` that uses same `strategist-forecaster.md` prompt\n- Use `OPENAI_API_KEY` from `.env` (read via `src/env.js`)\n- Return same shape as Claude: `{ estimated_probability, direction, edge, confidence, reasoning }`\n\n### 2. Run in parallel in `src/consensus.js`\n```js\nconst [claudeResult, gpt4oResult] = await Promise.all([\n  strategist().callForecaster(market, signals),\n  strategist().callGpt4oForecaster(market, signals)\n]);\nconst avgProb = (claudeResult.estimated_probability + gpt4oResult.estimated_probability) / 2;\n```\n\n### 3. Calibration logging per model\n- Log each model's prediction separately in `calibration_log`\n- Add `model` column: `claude-sonnet-4-6` | `gpt-4o` | `ensemble`\n- This lets us compare Brier scores per model once trades resolve\n- Eventually: weight by historical Brier score instead of simple average\n\n### 4. Kelly sizing\n- Keep crypto Kelly at 0.4× (ensemble reduces uncertainty vs single model)\n- Once calibration shows one model consistently outperforms, increase weight\n\n## Cost Estimate\n- GPT-4o: ~$0.003–0.01 per market eval via OpenAI API\n- Crypto markets evaluated maybe 5–15/day → ~$0.05–0.15/day\n- Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY` — actual API credits, not Max subscription\n- Alternative: route via OpenRouter to avoid direct OpenAI account\n\n## Do Not Build Until\n- 10+ resolved trades in `calibration_log`\n- Confirmed single-Claude calibration baseline (Brier score)\n- March 31 positions resolve → mid-April earliest\n\n## Files to Touch\n- `src/strategist.js` — add GPT-4o call\n- `src/consensus.js` → `evaluateSingleForecaster()` — parallel calls + average\n- `src/calibration.js` — add `model` column tracking\n- `data/polymarket.db` — migration: add `model` column to `calibration_log`\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-20 22:03)\nThe plan is written. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n**Built:** A detailed build plan at `polymarket-trading/plans/llm-ensemble-crypto.md` for adding GPT-4o as a parallel forecaster alongside Claude for crypto markets.\n\n**Why it's blocked now:** The calibration_log has 0 resolved trades. The task spec requires 10+ resolved trades to establish a single-Claude Brier score baseline before adding a second model — otherwise there's nothing to compare the ensemble against. March 31 positions need to resolve first, making mid-April the earliest start.\n\n**What the plan covers:**\n- Adding `openai` SDK and a `callGpt4oForecaster()` function in `strategist.js` that reuses the same prompt and market context as Claude\n- Parallel execution in `consensus.js` — both models run simultaneously, results averaged, with graceful fallback if one fails\n- Per-model calibration tracking — a `model` column on `calibration_log` so each model's Brier score can be compared independently\n- Cost controls ($5/month ceiling with Telegram alert), Kelly stays at 0.4× until ensemble is proven\n- Phase 2 path: once 30+ ensemble trades resolve, weight by inverse Brier score instead of simple average\n\n**What to do next:**\n1. Wait for March 31 crypto positions to resolve\n2. Run `scripts/train-calibration.py` to compute single-Claude Brier score\n3. Add `OPENAI_API_KEY` to `~/.openclaw/workspace/.env`\n4. Once prerequisites are met, implement from the plan (or create an MC task to trigger it)",
      "labels": [
        "polymarket",
        "ai",
        "crypto"
      ],
      "priority": "medium",
      "_id": "card_1774012985080",
      "createdAt": 1774012985080,
      "updatedAt": 1774277450525,
      "executorStatus": "completed",
      "completedAt": 1774167521400
    },
    {
      "column": "done",
      "order": 5,
      "title": "[Polymarket] REMINDER: Build LLM Ensemble After March 31",
      "description": "## Trigger Conditions (all must be true before building)\n\n- [ ] March 31 positions fully resolved (SOL $100 NO, SOL $80 YES, BTC $65K NO, ETH $1,800 NO)\n- [ ] 10+ resolved trades logged in `calibration_log`\n- [ ] Run `node src/index.js calibration` — see Brier score for single-Claude baseline\n- [ ] Verdict is CALIBRATED or OVERCONFIDENT (not INSUFFICIENT DATA)\n\n## Then Build\nSee card: **[Polymarket] LLM Ensemble for Crypto — Build Plan** for full instructions.\n\n## Why We're Waiting\nEnsemble improvement only measurable against baseline. Without resolved trades, we'd be adding complexity + API costs with no way to verify it's actually better than single Claude. Mid-April is the earliest realistic start date.\n\n## When Ready\nDelete this card and start building the ensemble. Expected build time: 1 session.\n\n---\n**Auto-executed by Task Executor** (2026-03-20 22:05)\nClear picture. Here's the situation:\n\n**This task cannot be executed yet.** It's a reminder with hard prerequisites, none of which are met:\n\n- **Today is March 20** — March 31 positions haven't resolved yet\n- **0 resolved trades** in `calibration_log` (need 10+)\n- **Paper trading just started today** (2026-03-20)\n- The ensemble build plan already exists at `agents/polymarket-trading/plans/llm-ensemble-crypto.md` — it's ready to go once conditions are met\n\nThis card is working exactly as intended: it's a gate that prevents premature optimization. The ensemble (Claude + GPT-4o) would add complexity and API costs with no way to measure if it's actually better than single-Claude until we have a Brier score baseline from resolved trades.\n\n**Earliest realistic execution: mid-April 2026**, after March 31 crypto positions resolve and enough trades accumulate in the calibration log.\n\nNo action needed — the card should stay on the board as-is until the trigger conditions flip true.",
      "labels": [
        "polymarket",
        "reminder"
      ],
      "priority": "low",
